The paper deals with theoretical properties of enforcing priors provided by generative deep neural networks via empirical risk minimization. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
